===Etymology===
{{inh|fr|frm|resver}}, from {{inh|fr|fro|resver||to consider, reflect, be delirious}} of {{unk.|fr|nocap=1}} origin. The ''Trésor de la langue française informatisé'' links it back either to an unattested {{m|fro|*esver||to wander}} or to Latin {{m|la|*reexvadō}}, from {{affix|la|re-|ex-|evadō|nocat=1}}<ref>{{R:TLFi|etym=1}}</ref>. The ''Französisches Etymologisches Wörterbuch'' links it back to {{m|la|*reexvagus}}, hence the same as the second proposal by the ''Trésor de la langue française informatisé''<ref>{{R:FEW|100|184|title=*reexvagus}}</ref>.

